Senate Judiciary 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB2434
Gardenhire
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2434 House Bill No. 2147*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 39-13-903(a)(6), is amended by
deleting "subdivision (a)(6)" in subdivisions (a)(6)(B) and (a)(6)(C) and substituting "subdivision
(a)(7)".
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 39-13-903(a), is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision (5) and renumbering the subsequent subdivisions:
(5) Knowingly uses an unmanned aircraft over the grounds of a public school
that serves students in any of the grades kindergarten through twelve (K-12) with the
intent to conduct surveillance of the school grounds without permission of a school
administrator, the director of schools, or the director's designee. This subdivision (a)(5)
does not apply to a law enforcement officer acting within the scope of the law
enforcement officer's lawful duties;
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 39-13-903, is amended by deleting
subsection (b) and substituting:
(b)
(1) An offense under subdivisions (a)(1)-(6) is a Class C misdemeanor.
(2) An offense under subdivision (a)(7) is a Class E felony.
SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 39-13-902, is amended by deleting
subdivision (a)(14) and substituting:
(14) Of public real property or a person on that property, except as prohibited by
§ 39-13-903(a)(5).
SA0756
013671
- 1 -

SECTION 5. This act takes effect July 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring it.
